revisions.rev:
The '''Convention on the Elimination of All Forms of Racial Discrimination''' (CERD) is a [[United Nations]] [[convention]] adopted and opened for signature and ratification by [[United Nations General Assembly]] resolution 2106 (XX) [[December 21]], [[1965]], and which entered into force [[January 4]], [[1969]].
==External links== *[http://www.unhchr.ch/html/menu3/b/d_icerd.htm Text of the resolution] on the sit of the Office of the High Commissioner for Human Rights. Links to information on status of ratifications, declarations and reservations, and the monitoring body, the [http://www.unhchr.ch/html/menu2/6/cerd.htm Committee on the Elimination of Racial Discrimination]
